cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.SY, cs.CY, cs.NE 

The paper discusses cyber securing a UAV communication, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of EEG signals to generate a key for encryption involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The development of a robust autopilot system for UAVs involves control systems (cs.SY) and cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). Finally, the validation of the system under malicious attack conditions involves neural networks (cs.NE) as the biometric system is based on EEG signals.
